  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. All 7 assessed credibility factors meet required levels; 6 factors are scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. Decision: Accepted. NOTE: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the structured Context of Use object is captured in the associated requirement and claim prose rather than in a dedicated hasContextOfUse node.",
